title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\ServiceAttachment
name: ServiceAttachment
description:
Represents a ServiceAttachment resource. A service attachment represents a service that a producer has exposed. It encapsulates the load balancer which fronts the service runs and a list of NAT IP ranges that the producers uses to represent the consumers connecting to the service. next tag = 20

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.ServiceAttachment

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.connected_endpoints
params.description: [Output Only] An array of connections for all the consumers connected to this service attachment.

params.name: data.connection_preference
params.description: The connection preference of service attachment. The value can be set to ACCEPT_AUTOMATIC. An ACCEPT_AUTOMATIC service attachment is one that always accepts the connection from consumer forwarding rules. Check the ConnectionPreference enum for the list of possible values.

params.name: data.consumer_accept_lists
params.description: Projects that are allowed to connect to this service attachment.

params.name: data.consumer_reject_lists
params.description: Projects that are not allowed to connect to this service attachment. The project can be specified using its id or number.

params.name: data.creation_timestamp
params.description: [Output Only] Creation timestamp in RFC3339 text format.

params.name: data.description
params.description: An optional description of this resource. Provide this property when you create the resource.

params.name: data.domain_names
params.description: If specified, the domain name will be used during the integration between the PSC connected endpoints and the Cloud DNS. For example, this is a valid domain name: "p.mycompany.com.". Current max number of domain names supported is 1.

params.name: data.enable_proxy_protocol
params.description: If true, enable the proxy protocol which is for supplying client TCP/IP address data in TCP connections that traverse proxies on their way to destination servers.

params.name: data.fingerprint
params.description: Fingerprint of this resource. A hash of the contents stored in this object. This field is used in optimistic locking. This field will be ignored when inserting a ServiceAttachment. An up-to-date fingerprint must be provided in order to patch/update the ServiceAttachment; otherwise, the request will fail with error 412 conditionNotMet. To see the latest fingerprint, make a get() request to retrieve the ServiceAttachment.

params.name: data.id
params.description: [Output Only] The unique identifier for the resource type. The server generates this identifier.

params.name: data.kind
params.description: [Output Only] Type of the resource. Always compute#serviceAttachment for service attachments.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Name of the resource. Provided by the client when the resource is created. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. Specifically, the name must be 1-63 characters long and match the regular expression [a-z]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])? which means the first character must be a lowercase letter, and all following characters must be a dash, lowercase letter, or digit, except the last character, which cannot be a dash.

params.name: data.nat_subnets
params.description: An array of URLs where each entry is the URL of a subnet provided by the service producer to use for NAT in this service attachment.

params.name: data.producer_forwarding_rule
params.description: The URL of a forwarding rule with loadBalancingScheme INTERNAL* that is serving the endpoint identified by this service attachment.

params.name: data.psc_service_attachment_id
params.description: [Output Only] An 128-bit global unique ID of the PSC service attachment.

params.name: data.region
params.description: [Output Only] URL of the region where the service attachment resides. This field applies only to the region resource. You must specify this field as part of the HTTP request URL. It is not settable as a field in the request body.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output Only] Server-defined URL for the resource.

params.name: data.target_service
params.description: The URL of a service serving the endpoint identified by this service attachment.
